The Biden-Harris Administration has been taking decisive action to restore and strengthen American democracy. They are prioritizing the fight to pass the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act to protect the right to vote. They are also convening a Summit for Democracy to strengthen commitment to democratic principles and practices worldwide. The administration has signed the bipartisan Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act and continues to work on the Build Back Better Act to improve people's lives and address challenges such as child care, housing, climate change, and healthcare. They are also focused on strengthening democracy by defending against authoritarianism, fighting corruption, and promoting respect for human rights. The administration is committed to protecting the sacred right to vote, promoting civic engagement, advancing workers' rights, and ensuring information integrity in technology. They are also combating domestic violent extremism and supporting independent media. The administration aims to prove that democracy can deliver tangible results, and they have been taking action to address the COVID-19 pandemic, rebuild infrastructure, and provide economic relief. They are also fighting corruption, promoting transparency, and advancing human rights, including racial justice, gender equity, LGBTQI+ equality, disability rights, Native American support, and combating hate crimes and human trafficking. The Biden-Harris Administration will continue to work on strengthening democracy and announce further actions and commitments throughout the year.